The most common reason for the application not showing up (white screen) in this environment is a version mismatch in the `react-router-dom` import or the AI service initializing too early with an invalid key.

I will fix this by:
1.  **`index.html`**: Correcting the `react-router-dom` version to a stable release (v6.22.3).
2.  **`services/geminiService.ts`**: Delaying the initialization of the AI client so it doesn't crash the app instantly if the API key environment variable is missing.

# Updated files:

## index.html

Updated `react-router-dom` to version `6.22.3` to ensure compatibility and prevent routing errors that can cause a blank screen.

## services/geminiService.ts

Moved the `GoogleGenAI` initialization inside the `generateSchoolResponse` function. This prevents the application from crashing on startup if the API key isn't immediately available or valid.

```typescript
