To resolve the "unexpected error" and get your application running locally and ready for deployment, I will fix the JSX syntax error in `components/PageSections.tsx`.

The error `The character ">" is not valid inside a JSX element` occurs because `>>` was used directly in the code. In JSX, `>` must be escaped as `&gt;` or `{'>>'}`.

I will also ensure the `App.tsx` file is correctly set up with all imports.

# Updated files:

## components/PageSections.tsx

I have escaped the `>>` characters in the `ModernCodingUI` component to `&gt;&gt;`. This fixes the build error.

