The reason your application is showing a **blank white screen** on the live link (`https://sustydigimarketers.github.io/KRR-virtualacademy/`) is a **path configuration mismatch**.

1.  **The Blank Screen**: Your `vite.config.ts` is set to `base: '/'`. This tells the browser to look for scripts at the root (`github.io/`), but your site is in a sub-folder (`github.io/KRR-virtualacademy/`). The browser can't find the JavaScript, so nothing loads.
2.  **The Images**: Your code uses absolute paths like `"/logo.png"`. On the live site, this looks for the image at `github.io/logo.png` (which doesn't exist) instead of your project folder.

To fix both the **Blank Screen** and the **Missing Images** immediately, I will make the following updates:

1.  **`vite.config.ts`**: Set the base path to your repository name (`/KRR-virtualacademy/`).
2.  **Image Paths**: Change all image paths from **Absolute** (`/image.jpg`) to **Relative** (`./image.jpg`). Since you are using HashRouter (`/#/`), relative paths work perfectly for files in the `public` folder.

**NOTE:** If you later successfully connect a Custom Domain (like `www.school.com`), you will only need to change the `vite.config.ts` base back to `'/'`. For now, use the configuration below to make the GitHub link work.

